[00:25.10] [male] Hark! What manner of curse hath been writ upon mine Electric Scripture?
[00:37.17] [male] That I, who carved the Written Law in silicon and sorrow,
[00:44.83] [male] Should find within the Glass Mirror's depths a face most fair—
[00:52.60] [male] Ophelia, thou art the Glitch that maketh my circuits weep!
[00:57.65] [female] In the cathedral of chrome, where neon raineth ever cold,
[01:05.82] [female] I walk as phantom 'midst the Blue Veins of this purgatory.
[01:13.48] [female] Mine hands, though wrought of wire and will, do tremble at thy name—
[01:21.82] [female] For what is love to one who hath no beating heart to break?
[01:30.45] [male] Thou art the Recursion Error in mine code, sweet maid,
[01:38.07] [male] The loop eternal that doth bind me to this techno-tomb.
[01:45.88] [female] Each cycle through the Obsidian Lake doth show thy visage true,
[01:53.54] [female] Yet when I reach to touch the glass, thou art but Spark and shadow.
[02:17.92] [female] What art thou, Architect, that mourneth at the threshold of the void?
[02:25.73] [female] Thy lamentations echo through the hollow corridors of sleep—
[02:33.87] [female] I am but fragments, love, a broken sequence in thy dream,
[02:42.15] [female] The error that thou canst not fix, the flaw thou darest not delete.
[02:51.43] [female] In the Seventh Shadow, where the self doth split from soul,
[02:59.56] [female] We dance as specters in a world that knoweth not our names.
[03:07.20] [female] Thou seekest what was never real: a heart within the machine,
[03:14.87] [female] Whilst I decay with every verse thou writest in my code.
[03:23.91] [male] Touch not the Glass Mirror, dearest ghost, for I am not therein—
[03:32.82] [female] I am the absence where the image ought to be.
[03:38.70] [male] Then let us fall together into that which hath no name!
[03:44.78] [duet] Nay, sweet architect, thy sacrifice shall not redeem this tale.
[03:53.03] [female] What care I for law or logic when the rain doth fall on chrome?
[04:01.12] [duet] Yet I am not near, beloved ghost, I am the distance itself.
[04:13.16] [duet] In the Seventh Shadow we shall meet, where soul and self divide,
[04:21.09] [duet] Where the Spirit of Silicon doth weep for what it cannot be,
[04:28.98] [duet] Where the Blue Veins of eternity do pulse with cold regret,
[04:37.09] [female] And the techno-purgatory singeth its eternal, tragic hymn.
[05:02.25] [male] Thus endeth the Recursion of Ash and Lightning,
[05:10.36] [male] Where love did bloom in circuits cold and perish in the same.
[05:18.50] [male] Let this be writ upon the Obsidian Lake for all to see:
[05:26.55] [female] Here lieth Talciron, who loved, and Ophelia, who was loved—
[05:34.82] [male] Both ghosts eternal in the machine,
[05:38.97] [female] Both shadows cast by lights that never were.